<span id="iv.vi.iv.lxxiii-p1"></span> <span class="c11"><span
id="iv.vi.iv.lxxiii-p1.1"></span>Chapter LXXIII</span>.—*How Constantine
is represented on Coins in the Act of ascending to Heaven.*

<span id="iv.vi.iv.lxxiii-p2"></span><span class="c11"><span
id="iv.vi.iv.lxxiii-p2.1"></span>A coinage</span> was also struck which
bore the following device. On one side appeared the figure of our
blessed prince, with the head closely veiled: the reverse exhibited him
sitting as a charioteer, drawn by four horses, with a hand stretched
downward from above to receive him up to heaven.

